    "summary": "I am a PhD candidate at Delft University of Technology working on Internet of Robotic Things where I combine mobile networked robotic systems with IoT applications of sensing and wireless communication. My PhD is supported by the European Project InSecTT (Intelligent Secure Trustable Things) which focuses on developing edge processing algorithms on resource constrained devices under the purview of creating white box AI which can be utilized across industries. I am also the co-founder of ZED or Zero Energy Development, a TU Delft startup focusing on Energy Harvesting and batteryless wireless IoT technology. I also love making things and am a founding member of Delft Open Hardware, a community which fosters the spirit of open source and freedom in hardware innovation and a mentor to the Robotics Student Association in Delft",
