                    "company": "CERN",
                    "description": "I was selected to participate in an intensive summer innovation programme held at CERN IdeaSquare, Geneva where we were tasked with finding alternative socially beneficial applications for CERN technology. My team and I worked on ultra high accuracy, low frequency seismic MEMS sensors originally developed for gravitational wave experiments which we re-imagined as instruments to improve PET Scan imaging. I had the pleasure to work alongside a wonderfully diverse team of TU Delft honours students. \n\nThe culmination of our work was published as an article in the CERN IdeaSquare Journal of Experimental Innovation. In it we explore the first stages of a new product development process, drawing insights into an optimal approach to follow for coming up with new ideas. Illustrating this process of translating a CERN technology into an application which benefits the society at large, the paper exemplifies the importance of open innovation in the idea generation and selection processes.",
